Knightswood was also home to the wizard
Cauldigurn the Black, a mild-mannered
war wizard known for the battle
spells he devised, all of which combined
harmful effects with an area of conjured
darkness and were the origin of his nickname.
Cauldigurn died in Sembia 22 winters
ago, and his small cottage stands
roofless and empty. Somewhere around it,
locals insist, is an invisible gate to his real
home, where his spellbooks, magical
items, and wealth presumably still lie. Several
war wizards have thoroughly searched
the cottage and the woods around, but no
trace of a magical way to elsewhere.or
any magic at all.has yet been found.
